      <hedline>
        <hl1>Re: Benedict Arnold</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Mavis letter holds Jamie Malanowski failed to mention 1955 movie Scarlet Coat in July 2 article about Revolutionary War movies (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>One small omission in Jamie Malanowski's article concerning the Revolutionary War as depicted in the movies [''The Revolutionary War Is Lost on Hollywood,'' July 2]: there was a large Hollywood film made about Benedict Arnold in 1955, ''The Scarlet Coat,'' starring Cornel Wilde, Michael Wilding, George Sanders and Anne Francis. It was directed by the veteran action director John Sturges. It was also a box office flop.</p>
        <p>PAUL MAVIS  Maumee, Ohio</p>
      </block>
